text: Quan Xin (born November 24, 1996) is a Chinese slalom canoeist who competes in the K-1 event. He won a gold medal at the 2018 Asian Games and a silver at the 2016 Asian Championships. ==References== Category:Chinese male canoeists Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Asian Games medalists in canoeing Category:Canoeists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for China Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games
